-- India Sugar Exports at 3.2 Million Tons, FCStone Says
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2012-02-24T01:42:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/india-sugar-exports-at-3-2-million-tons-fcstone-says-correct-.html
(Corrects import and production numbers in story first
published yesterday.)  India ’s exports of sugar are
expected to total 3.2 million metric tons in 2011-2012, compared
with 2.3 million tons in 2010-2011, according to INTL FCStone
Inc. The nation’s production is forecast to be 26 million tons
in 2011-2012, compared with 24.4 million tons in 2010-2011,
Mario Silveira, senior risk management consultant, said at a
conference in  Singapore  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glenys Sim in Singapore at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jake Lloyd-Smith at 
 jlloydsmith@bloomberg.net  